The paper focuses on the design of a mobile imaging system for early detection of melanoma using smartphone-captured visible light images. This involves addressing challenges related to image distortions and resource constraints on the smartphone. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by human-computer interaction (cs.HC), multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG).
